00:39:53.740 --> 00:39:55.540
We gotta walk with God.

00:39:55.540 --> 00:39:58.180
We gotta have that testimony that Noah had.

00:39:58.180 --> 00:40:00.580
We look at that testimony of Noah and we say.

00:40:00.580 --> 00:40:07.100
I say, man, in the midst of such a time, Noah found grace in the eyes of the Lord.

00:40:07.100 --> 00:40:14.300
He was a just man, he was perfect in his generations, and it summarizes it this way, that Noah walked

00:40:14.300 --> 00:40:15.980
with God.

00:40:15.980 --> 00:40:18.980
God's called you, God's called me.

00:40:18.980 --> 00:40:25.340
In the midst of whatever the wickedness might be around us, to walk with God, to walk with

00:40:25.340 --> 00:40:30.260
God, and to be a light in this dark world.

00:40:30.260 --> 00:40:35.900
This evening let's be like Noah, let's not make excuses and say, well, it's just so hard.

00:40:35.900 --> 00:40:42.340
I understand it can be hard, but with God, with the help of God, it's possible.

00:40:42.340 --> 00:40:46.260
It is possible that we can walk with Him in this dark world.

00:40:46.260 --> 00:40:47.260
Amen?

00:40:47.260 --> 00:40:48.260
